Additionally, the paper leverages parallelization and optimization techniques commonly used in machine learning. 

The paper may also belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category as Gaussian processes are a popular model in AI research. 

Computer vision (cs.CV) is another possible sub-category as Gaussian processes have been used in image processing and computer vision tasks. 

Data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) is a possible sub-category as the paper discusses partitioning and distributing kernel matrix multiplies, which involves designing efficient data structures and algorithms. 

Finally, neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) is a possible sub-category as the paper discusses optimization techniques like linear conjugate gradients, which are commonly used in neural network training.
